ublic schools are run by the government, you may elect whomever you choose to be on the board, etc., but that is where your control over your child's education ends.  Once they are elected they may do as they please and you're stuck with them until the next election when you can hopefully vote them out.  With the private schooling system parents are heard because it's more like a business transaction, if you think you are not getting what you paid for you can guarantee your concern(s) will be addressed!  I cannot believe the arrogance of the author of this article, everybody already pays for public school through their taxes, people who cough up the extra cash to send their children to private schools are supporting the public schools whether they'd like to or not! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1083" language="en" documentId="3745" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Yuppers720" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:39PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="12" thumbsDown="0" origId="3745" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1083"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>